Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport asmphora. Oval handle from neck join to moderate turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine red-brown; dull slip.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name, Aristeidas Athens, Agora SS11555, is similarly retrograde and scruffy, but does not have lunate letters. There is a 'patch' of stamps with this form of 'Knidianising' scrawl at this period.
